and maybe you're wrong.

1110
01:27:04,519 --> 01:27:08,011
- We'll just have to try them out, I guess.
- But, Huck, you can't.

1111
01:27:08,122 --> 01:27:10,317
Roberta's never put out clothes like those.

1112
01:27:10,425 --> 01:27:12,450
Roberta's is in new hands now.

1113
01:27:14,596 --> 01:27:17,588
But this is like the mode
two seasons back.

1114
01:27:17,799 --> 01:27:19,858
I know, but I liked them better then.

1115
01:27:19,968 --> 01:27:22,027
But nobody will buy them.

1116
01:27:22,870 --> 01:27:26,306
Well, you'd be laughed out of Paris
if you did a thing like that.

1117
01:27:26,374 --> 01:27:28,968
The trend is away from such styles.

1118
01:27:29,043 --> 01:27:31,603
- I'm not interested in the trend.
- But you've got to be.

1119
01:27:31,679 --> 01:27:34,512
You don't understand.
You're giving a fashion show next week.

1120
01:27:34,616 --> 01:27:36,481
Every couturier in Europe
is going to be watching.

1121
01:27:36,551 --> 01:27:38,348
You can't afford to show
models like those.

1122
01:27:38,453 --> 01:27:41,013
Well, of course you cannot.
Stephanie is right!

1123
01:27:41,122 --> 01:27:42,885
What does it matter
as long as they're pretty?

1124
01:27:42,991 --> 01:27:44,686
But clothes must be more than pretty.

1125
01:27:44,792 --> 01:27:47,454
Look, the trouble with that is it...

1126
01:27:48,563 --> 01:27:50,656
It fits in the wrong places.

1127
01:27:51,499 --> 01:27:55,128
Such a pity.
The famous Roberta to go second rate.

1128
01:27:55,303 --> 01:27:58,466
- Roberta's will never go second rate.
- Who is to stop it?

1129
01:27:58,539 --> 01:28:01,633
The fashion show next week
will be a colossal flop.

1130
01:28:01,809 --> 01:28:03,470
Maybe we should call off
the fashion show.

1131
01:28:03,544 --> 01:28:04,636
I think so.

1132
01:28:04,712 --> 01:28:07,681
- We might better put on a good one.
- Now you're talking, Stephanie.

1133
01:28:07,749 --> 01:28:11,014
We'll put on a better-than-good one.
We'll give them some entertainment, too.

1134
01:28:11,085 --> 01:28:12,677
- How about your band?
- That's a great idea.

1135
01:28:12,754 --> 01:28:13,880
- Yeah.
- We'll bring over my band.

1136
01:28:13,988 --> 01:28:15,387
- A musical fashion show.
- Yes, that's it.

1137
01:28:15,490 --> 01:28:18,550
- It'll be marvelous.
- And you can make the new designs.

1138
