<i>"faller-downer" on the courses</i>

1142
01:28:59,701 --> 01:29:03,762
<i>Now take the dowager who is glad</i>
<i>to leave her watchman for tea</i>

1143
01:29:04,238 --> 01:29:07,799
<i>She'll wear this patriotic plaid</i>
<i>and meet that Scotchman for tea</i>

1144
01:29:08,476 --> 01:29:11,377
<i>When summertime begins</i>
<i>this costume always wins</i>

1145
01:29:11,446 --> 01:29:14,813
<i>When 50 million little Frenchmen</i>
<i>clap their fins</i>

1146
01:29:15,450 --> 01:29:18,908
<i>For hunting grouse or quail</i>
<i>Roberta ran up this suit</i>

1147
01:29:19,120 --> 01:29:23,420
<i>The modest price includes</i>
<i>the bag, the gun and two ducks to shoot</i>

1148
01:29:23,791 --> 01:29:26,760
<i>And should Amelia Earhart care</i>
<i>to get a breath of air</i>

1149
01:29:26,828 --> 01:29:30,320
<i>this is the last thing in the world</i>
<i>she'd ever wear</i>

1150
01:29:35,837 --> 01:29:40,297
- Ladislaw, are we gathering later?
- The Princess begs to be excused.

1151
01:29:40,408 --> 01:29:43,343
We are leaving for Rome
immediately the showing is finished.

1152
01:29:48,783 --> 01:29:50,614
<i>It is the hour for dry martinis</i>

1153
01:29:50,685 --> 01:29:53,279
<i>The park is full of little Fords</i>
<i>and Isotta Fraschinis</i>

1154
01:29:53,354 --> 01:29:55,822
<i>The Ritz bar is serving caviar and weenies</i>

1155
01:29:55,923 --> 01:29:57,356
<i>Madame is there</i>

1156
01:29:57,458 --> 01:30:00,120
<i>And from Roberta she has something</i>
<i>that is too divine on</i>

1157
